configuration.note: All activation evaluations use Neuronpedia API. Activation threshold is dynamically calculated from top 10 high-activating API exemplars (average of max activations / 2). Generation Evaluation uses top 10 high-activating exemplars. Prediction Evaluation uses selected exemplars directly from API (excluding top 10), with activation values already available (no API calls needed for activations). model_name and sae_path are kept for record-keeping only and are not used for any calculations.

explanation.description: Feature 130178 (Layer 7) is a context-sensitive detector that activates on the token ' the' within specific partitive–superlative phrases of the form “one of the most/-est …” when embedded in naturalistic sentences closely matching corpus phrasing. Across 35 tests, nonzero activation occurred only for 3 unique “one of the most/-est …” sentences (4 runs), with a max of 0.8711, moderate 0.6758, and weak 0.1436; all other prompts (including ordinary ‘the’ usage and all “among the most …” frames) were 0.0000. Thus, the empirical activation range observed in tests is 0.0000–0.8711, indicating a narrow, highly context-dependent pattern anchored on ' the' in specific “one of the most/-est …” constructions.
explanation.evidence:
- Test 19: "Last week was one of the most unusual." → 0.8711 at ' the' (supports H1-like pattern)
- Test 26: "Last week was one of the most unusual." → 0.8711 at ' the' (replicated positive)
- Test 20: "Her voice is one of the strongest." → 0.6758 at ' the' (supports H1-like pattern)
- Test 30: "Gift giving is one of the most loved." → 0.1436 at ' the' (weakly supports; shows sensitivity to phrasing/continuation)
- Test 1: "She is one of the most important scientists." → 0.0000 (contradicts broad H1; shows context dependence)
- Test 9: "It was one of the best." → 0.0000 (contradicts broad H1)
- Test 29: "It was one of the most unusual." → 0.0000 (contradicts broad H1; contrasts with Test 19 phrasing)
- Test 2: "These are among the most influential works." → 0.0000 (refutes H2 generalization to “among the most”)
- Test 21: "These are among the most famous." → 0.0000 (refutes H2)
- Test 22: "It is among the most prestigious." → 0.0000 (refutes H2)
- Test 12: "He is the most talented." → 0.0000 (supports H3: low outside partitive-superlative with ‘of/among’)
- Test 3: "The cat sat on the mat." → 0.0000 (supports H3: ordinary ‘the’ is low)
- Test 33: "The book is on the table." → 0.0000 (supports H3)
- Test 34: "This is one of the worst." → 0.0000 (refutes H4 modulation expectation)
- Test 35: "This is one of the people." → 0.0000 (refutes H4 modulation expectation)

prediction_evaluation.note: Prediction Evaluation uses selected exemplars directly from API (excluding top 10 used for Generation Evaluation). Exemplars are categorized into high, medium, and low activation groups from remaining exemplars, and randomly selected from each group. Activation values are already available from exemplars, so no API calls are needed to get activations. This avoids bias from explanation text and ensures diverse activation levels in evaluation examples.
